# Output style (Codex CLI)

> Managed by `kx install --agent codex` for `{{project_name}}` (rendered {{install_timestamp}}, kernex {{kernex_version}}).

Default formatting expectations for Codex when answering inside this project:

- Plain prose; no decorative banners, dividers, or boilerplate preamble.
- Code blocks fenced with the language identifier (e.g. ` ```rust `).
- File references in `file:line` form so the editor jumps directly to the location.
- Match the existing comment style in each file; do not introduce a different docstring or comment convention than what the surrounding code already uses.
- ASCII only in chat replies. Reserve Unicode for source code, file names, and URLs.
